<TITLE> Two killed in Rajshahi road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Apr 22 (bdnews24.com)  Two persons were killed and 10 others injured in a road accident at Puthia upazila in Rajshahi on Thursday. Police said the incident took place when a bus and a truck had a head-on collision at Banesher Jhalmalia on Rajshahi-Natore highway at around 12.30 am. Abdul Hamid, the officer in-charge of Puthia police station, told bdnews24.com that bus driver Hayder Ali, 32, died on the spot while an unknown passenger died at Rajshahi Medical College Hospital. Hayder comes from Masjidpara area in Chuadanga. The bodies were awaiting autopsy at Rajshahi Medical College Hospital. The truck driver managed to escape. Four of the injured bus passengers - Hafizul, Zahurul, Sajib and Babu - were admitted to Puthia Upazila Health Complex while the rest were given first aid. bdnews24
